    {
      "id": "/page/0/Text/2",
      "block_type": "Text",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"Text\">This article is organized as follows. We first provide a description of the Altiplano option and discuss the financial motivations for and strategies of its usage. We then discuss modeling, valuation, and risk issues that Altiplano options share with all Mountain Range options, and conclude with a brief analysis of the risk profile that is unique to it. We remark that although the following discussion holds for a wide class of assets, such as foreign exchange (FX) and commodities, these options are traded mostly on baskets of stocks.</p>",
      "page": 353,
