    {
      "id": "/page/0/TextInlineMath/5",
      "block_type": "TextInlineMath",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"TextInlineMath\">More precisely, given a portfolio, or a basket of <i>n</i> stocks, let <i>Si(t)</i> be the price of the stock <i>i</i> = 1<i>,...,n</i> at time <i>t</i>, with 0 being the start of the option and <i>T</i> its maturity. The payoff is</p>",
      "page": 353,
      "polygon": [
