    {
      "id": "/page/0/Text/9",
      "block_type": "Text",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"Text\">As in single-name barriers, since <i>IB</i> is always less than 1, the payoff, and thus the risk, are lower than for standard options on baskets, which makes their premiums lower as well (assuming <i>C</i> is small or zero). The lower premium makes it more attractive when used as a hedge, for example.</p>",
